{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T17:59:10.053Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cross-Entropy"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a fundamental measure in information theory that quantifies the average number of bits needed to encode events when using an "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "estimated probability distribution"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (predicted by a model) instead of the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "true distribution"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (actual data)—it measures how \"surprised\" you'd be if you used the wrong encoding scheme, and serves as the primary loss function for classification and generative models in machine learning because minimizing cross-entropy is equivalent to minimizing KL divergence between true and predicted distributions."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Cross-Entropy — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mathematical definition:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cross-Entropy"}, {"type": "text", "text": " between two probability distributions "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "P"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (true) and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Q"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (predicted/estimated) is:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "H(P, Q) = - Σ P(x) × log(Q(x))"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "P(x)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = true probability of event x (actual data distribution)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Q(x)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = estimated probability of event x (model's prediction)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "log"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = logarithm (base 2 for bits, base e for nats)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Negative sign"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = ensures positive value (since log of probability < 1 is negative)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[tensortonic](https://www.tensortonic.com/ml-math/information-theory/cross-entropy)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Alternative form (for classification):"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a single sample with true label y and predicted probabilities ŷ:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "H(y, ŷ) = - Σ yᵢ × log(ŷᵢ)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "y"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = true label (one-hot encoded: [1, 0, 0,...])\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ŷ"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = predicted probabilities (e.g., [0.7, 0.2, 0.1])"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[training.continuumlabs](https://training.continuumlabs.ai/training/the-fine-tuning-process/hyperparameters/cross-entropy-loss)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Intuitive meaning:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-Entropy = expected message length (bits) when using wrong encoding\n\nImagine you're encoding weather data:\n- True distribution P: Actual weather probabilities (70% sunny, 30% rainy)\n- Estimated Q: Your model's predicted probabilities (50% sunny, 50% rainy)\n\nCross-Entropy = extra bits needed per message when using Q instead of P [web:307][web:308]\n\nThe \"cross\" refers to using P to weight but Q to compute information [web:310]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": \"Cross-entropy measures uncertainty using a different (predicted) distribution instead of the true distribution\"."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-Entropy vs Entropy vs KL Divergence"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The relationship:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-Entropy = Entropy + KL Divergence\n\nH(P, Q) = H(P) + D_KL(P||Q) [web:308][web:310][web:313]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Breakdown:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Concept"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Formula"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Meaning"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Entropy H(P)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "-Σ P(x) log P(x)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Uncertainty using "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "true"}, {"type": "text", "text": " distribution (optimal encoding)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cross-Entropy H(P,Q)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "-Σ P(x) log Q(x)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Uncertainty using "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "estimated"}, {"type": "text", "text": " distribution (wrong encoding)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "KL Divergence D_KL(P"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": " "}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Q)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Σ P(x) log(P/Q)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Extra bits needed when using Q instead of P"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[youtube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ErfnhcEV1O8)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Derivation:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "H(P, Q) = - Σ P(x) × log(Q(x))\n        = - Σ P(x) × [log(P(x)) - log(P(x)/Q(x))]\n        = - Σ P(x) × log(P(x)) + Σ P(x) × log(P(x)/Q(x))\n        = H(P) + D_KL(P||Q)\n\nTherefore:\nCross-Entropy = Entropy + KL Divergence [web:310][web:313]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why this matters:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Since H(P) is constant (data is fixed):\n→ Minimizing Cross-Entropy = Minimizing KL Divergence [web:310][web:311]\n\nThe entropy of the true distribution doesn't depend on predictions, so optimizing cross-entropy focuses entirely on reducing the distance between distributions [web:310]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": \"Minimizing cross-entropy is the same as minimizing KL divergence from predicted to true (they're equivalent up to an additive constant)\"."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to compute — Step-by-step examples"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 1: Binary classification (single sample)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "True label: y = [1, 0] (Class 0 is correct)\nPredicted: ŷ = [0.7, 0.3]\n\nCross-Entropy = - Σ yᵢ × log(ŷᵢ)\n              = -[1 × log(0.7) + 0 × log(0.3)]\n              = -[1 × (-0.357) + 0]\n              = 0.357 nats\n\nInterpretation: Model predicts 70% for true class → low loss (good)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 2: Multi-class classification"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "True label: y = [1, 0, 0] (Class 0)\nPredicted: ŷ = [0.1, 0.7, 0.2] (wrong prediction)\n\nCross-Entropy = -[1 × log(0.1) + 0 × log(0.7) + 0 × log(0.2)]\n              = -[1 × (-2.303) + 0 + 0]\n              = 2.303 nats\n\nInterpretation: Model predicts 10% for true class → high loss (bad)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 3: Cross-Entropy vs Entropy + KL"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "True distribution P: [0.5, 0.3, 0.2]\nPredicted Q: [0.4, 0.4, 0.2]\n\nStep 1: Entropy H(P)\nH(P) = -[0.5×log(0.5) + 0.3×log(0.3) + 0.2×log(0.2)]\n     = 1.483 nats\n\nStep 2: KL Divergence D_KL(P||Q)\nD_KL = [0.5×log(0.5/0.4) + 0.3×log(0.3/0.4) + 0.2×log(0.2/0.2)]\n     = 0.011 nats\n\nStep 3: Cross-Entropy H(P,Q)\nH(P,Q) = -[0.5×log(0.4) + 0.3×log(0.4) + 0.2×log(0.2)]\n       = 1.494 nats\n\nCheck: H(P) + D_KL = 1.483 + 0.011 = 1.494 = H(P,Q) ✓"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters — Importance in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-Entropy is the standard loss function for classification and generative models:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ML Application"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How cross-entropy applies"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Classification"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard loss (e.g., logistic regression, neural networks)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Language Models"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-entropy loss trains GPT, BERT to predict next tokens"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "VAEs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-entropy in reconstruction loss for binary data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "GANs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Minimize cross-entropy between real and generated distributions"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Autoregressive Models"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Scaling laws for cross-entropy loss in image/text generation"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Real example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Training GPT-4 uses cross-entropy loss to minimize differences between predicted and actual next tokens across billions of training examples."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Python implementation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-Entropy for classification:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# True labels (one-hot)\ny_true = np.array([1, 0, 0])  # Class 0 is correct\n\n# Predicted probabilities\ny_pred = np.array([0.7, 0.2, 0.1])\n\n# Cross-Entropy loss\nloss = -np.sum(y_true * np.log(y_pred))\nprint(f\"Cross-Entropy loss: {loss:.3f}\")  # ≈ 0.357 nats"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Binary Cross-Entropy (BCE):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# True label (0 or 1)\ny_true = 1\n\n# Predicted probability (for class 1)\ny_pred = 0.7\n\n# Binary Cross-Entropy\nloss = -(y_true * np.log(y_pred) + (1 - y_true) * np.log(1 - y_pred))\nprint(f\"BCE loss: {loss:.3f}\")  # ≈ 0.357 nats"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Categorical Cross-Entropy (multiple classes):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\ndef categorical_cross_entropy(y_true, y_pred):\n    \"\"\"y_true: one-hot encoded, y_pred: probabilities\"\"\"\n    return -np.sum(y_true * np.log(y_pred))\n\n# Example\ny_true = np.array([0, 1, 0])  # Class 1\ny_pred = np.array([0.2, 0.6, 0.2])\n\nloss = categorical_cross_entropy(y_true, y_pred)\nprint(f\"Categorical CE: {loss:.3f}\")  # ≈ 0.511 nats"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-Entropy as Loss Function"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why cross-entropy works better than MSE:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cross-Entropy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MSE"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Penalizes wrong predictions"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Strongly penalizes low probability for true class"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Only penalizes squared difference"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient behavior"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large gradient when prediction wrong (fast learning)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Small gradient when far from target"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Probabilistic"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Models output probabilities"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Models output continuous values"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key insight"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Cross-entropy is the standard classification loss because it directly penalizes the probability assigned to the true class."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient of cross-entropy:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For classification with softmax:\n∂L/∂ŷᵢ = (ŷᵢ - yᵢ) / ŷᵢ\n\nWhen prediction is wrong (ŷᵢ small for true class):\n→ Large gradient → strong learning signal [web:310]\n\nWhen prediction is correct (ŷᵢ large for true class):\n→ Small gradient → fine-tuning [web:310]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Special cases"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Binary Cross-Entropy (BCE)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For binary classification (2 classes):\n\nL = -(y × log(ŷ) + (1-y) × log(1-ŷ))\n\nWhere:\n- y = true label (0 or 1)\n- ŷ = predicted probability for class 1 [web:310]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Categorical Cross-Entropy"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For multi-class classification (K classes):\n\nL = - Σ yᵢ × log(ŷᵢ)\n\nWhere:\n- y = one-hot encoded true labels\n- ŷ = predicted probabilities for K classes [web:310]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Perplexity"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Perplexity = exp(Cross-Entropy)\n\nMeasures how \"confused\" the model is:\n- Low perplexity = model confident (good)\n- High perplexity = model uncertain (bad) [web:309]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cross-Entropy formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": H(P,Q) = -Σ P(x) log Q(x)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Meaning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Extra bits needed when using wrong encoding (Q instead of P)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cross-Entropy = Entropy + KL"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": H(P,Q) = H(P) + D_KL(P||Q)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Minimize CE = Minimize KL"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Since H(P) is constant, optimizing CE focuses on reducing distance"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Classification loss"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Standard loss function for neural networks, logistic regression"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Binary CE"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": L = -(y log(ŷ) + (1-y) log(1-ŷ))"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Categorical CE"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": L = -Σ yᵢ log(ŷᵢ)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient behavior"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Large when prediction wrong (fast learning)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Better than MSE"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Directly penalizes probability for true class"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Language models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Cross-entropy loss trains GPT, BERT"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Perplexity"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": exp(Cross-Entropy) = model confusion"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Perfect prediction"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": If Q = P, cross-entropy = entropy (no extra bits)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For Generative AI, cross-entropy is absolutely fundamental: it's the primary loss function for training language models like GPT-4 (predicting next tokens), classification models, and generative architectures because minimizing cross-entropy directly minimizes KL divergence between true and predicted distributions, ensuring the model learns to generate data that matches reality; understanding cross-entropy is essential for mastering how neural networks learn from data."}]}]}}